#datetimepicker.panel
	.panel-header
		h3.panel-title Bootstrap Date/Timepicker
	.panel-body
		p Bootstrap Date/Timepicker is a plugin for choosing date and time with stylization feature.
		p Plugin and style sheets linking occurs when the element that matches the #[code [data-datetimepicker&#93;] selector is present on the page.

		p Plugin operation example:
		.mt-1
			input.form-control( type='text', name='datetime', data-datetimepicker )
		p See more plugin operation examples on the following page: #[a( href='plugin-inputs.html' ) Plugin Inputs].

		p Markup example:
		pre.highlight.html.scroller.scroller-horizontal
			= '<input class="form-control" type="text" name="datetime" data-datetimepicker>'

		p This template provides a #[code data-datetimepicker] attribute for Bootstrap Date/Timepicker that can accept a JSON object with the plugin parameters, e.g.:
		pre.highlight.html.scroller.scroller-horizontal
			= '<input ... data-datetimepicker=\'{ "format": "LT", "inline": true, "target": "#time3" }\'>'

		p #[code inline: true] parameter in #[code data-datetimepicker] attribute implies a mandatory availability of #[code target] parameter with field selector, where the value will be written.
		p All available parameters of the plugin can be viewed on #[a( href="http://eonasdan.github.io/bootstrap-datetimepicker/" ) Bootstrap Date/Timepicker] website.
